<p>109. Intersectionality is also demonstrated by work methods in terms of the joint 
communications, country visits and reports undertaken by the SRVAW with other special 
procedures. Only a small fraction of the total number of communications issued by the SRVAW 
annually are sent singly; the bulk of the communications are sent jointly with other special 
mechanisms.<b>181</b> During the past two years, a large majority of the joint communications have 
been sent with the special thematic mechanisms on torture, human rights defenders, trafficking, 
and freedom of opinion and expression,<b>182</b> &#8220;indicating a convergence between diverse forms of 
                                                 
</p>
