period of 60 days is allowed for the governments to reply to allegation letters, as a result of 
which communications cannot be made public before the expiration of 60 days; if this period 
overlaps with the time when the SRVAW submits her report to the HRC, such communications 
do not get published in the year they are sent, and are instead reflected in the report due in the 
