discrimination and link State accountability for human rights under various treaty bodies&#8221;.<b>189</b> 
Notably, such an approach makes visible the continuum of violence and discrimination that 
captures more fully the consequences of intersectional discrimination. The SRVAW has applied 
this in relation to female refugees and internally displaced persons (IDPs), to formulate 
